This paper is about end-to-end task-oriented dialog systems, which are typically studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically in the subfield of conversational AI (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel model that incorporates knowledge bases, which is a common challenge in NLP and AI research. Therefore, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. The model is a neural generative model, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of multi-hop attention, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
